This error occurs when using a template string and forgetting to enclose a variable or expression inside curly braces. For example:

```
const name = "Alice";
console.log(`Hello, name!`);
```

In the example above, the variable `name` is not enclosed in curly braces. Therefore, the output will be "Hello, name!" instead of "Hello, Alice!". 

To fix this, simply enclose the variable or expression in curly braces:

```
const name = "Alice";
console.log(`Hello, ${name}!`);
```

这个错误的解决方法是在模板字符串中用花括号将所有变量或表达式括起来。以前面提到的示例代码为例：

```
const name = "Alice";
console.log(`Hello, name!`);
```

应该改为：

```
const name = "Alice";
console.log(`Hello, ${name}!`);
```

这样就可以将变量`name`放进花括号中，使输出变为"Hello, Alice!"，并且不再报错。

